[267.747505, "o", "BASH(1)        General Commands Manual       BASH(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       bash - GNU Bourne-Again SHell\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m [options] [command_string | file]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mCOPYRIGHT\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       Bash  is  Copyright (C) 1989-2022 by the Free\u001b[m\r\n       Software Foundation, Inc.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mBash\u001b[0m is an \u001b[1msh\u001b[0m-compatible command language in‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m page bash(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[268.328487, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[268.328583, "o", "       terpreter  that  executes  commands read from\u001b[m\r\n       the standard input or from a file.  \u001b[1mBash\u001b[0m also\u001b[m\r\n       incorporates  useful  features  from the \u001b[4mKorn\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n       and \u001b[4mC\u001b[24m shells (\u001b[1mksh\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mcsh\u001b[0m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mBash\u001b[0m is intended to be a conformant implemen‐\u001b[m\r\n       tation  of the Shell and Utilities portion of\u001b[m\r\n       the IEEE POSIX specification  (IEEE  Standard\u001b[m\r\n       1003.1).  \u001b[1mBash\u001b[0m can be configured to be POSIX-\u001b[m\r\n       conformant by default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mOPTIONS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       All of  the  single-character  shell  options\u001b[m\r\n       documented  in  the  description  of  the \u001b[1mset\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7mpage bash(1) line 15 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[270.008737, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[270.008883, "o", "       builtin command, including \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m, can be used as\u001b[m\r\n       options  when the shell is invoked.  In addi‐\u001b[m\r\n       tion, \u001b[1mbash\u001b[0m interprets the  following  options\u001b[m\r\n       when it is invoked:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-c\u001b[0m        If  the  \u001b[1m-c\u001b[0m option is present, then\u001b[m\r\n                 commands are read  from  the  first\u001b[m\r\n                 non-option argument \u001b[4mcommand_string\u001b[24m.\u001b[m\r\n                 If there are  arguments  after  the\u001b[m\r\n                 \u001b[4mcommand_string\u001b[24m,  the first argument\u001b[m\r\n                 is assigned to \u001b[1m$0\u001b[0m and any remaining\u001b[m\r\n                 arguments are assigned to the posi‐\u001b[m\r\n                 tional parameters.  The  assignment\u001b[m\r\n                 to  \u001b[1m$0\u001b[0m  sets the name of the shell,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7mpage bash(1) line 29 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
